cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CY

The paper focuses on comparing the citation networks of bibliographic databases, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of digital information, including bibliographic databases. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the analysis and retrieval of information from large datasets, which is relevant to the study of citation networks. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories as they deal with the analysis and modeling of complex networks. Finally, cs.CY (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper uses graph theory to analyze the citation networks.
